title: Georgia Firm Recalls Chicken and Beef Products Due to Misbranding and an Undeclared Allergen
summary: WASHINGTON, Jan. 17, 2015 Sentry Food Solutions, a Tucker, Ga., establishment, is recalling approximately 14,130 pounds of chicken and beef products due to misbranding and an undeclared allergen, the U.S. Department of Agricultures Food Safety and Inspection Service (FSIS) announced today.
